{
  "stem": "22174.7",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Aye, yeah.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, Palestine-- the first time when I came to Palestine [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] was, for me, a shock, a culture shock.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] We were-- although we never were, neither my father, nor my family, or I were anytime real German patriots.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I  have an aversion, actually, against patriotism.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Because the patriots in Germany were mostly-- [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] their attitude was a national vanity.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And, right or wrong, you know, 'Deutschland, Deutschland uber Alles,' you know, Germany, Germany were everything.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "You know?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And-- the superiority of Germany and all this.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I have developed a real-- and then between the two wars-- from the-- from the end  of World War I until the Nazi-- Nazi regime, there was a strong-- a strong movement of pacifism, which was only in the-- only within the democratically inclined population.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Yes, the intellectuals, not all, but many intellectuals, many of them were Jews, professionals, working people that had-- that had suffered terribly losses during the war and after the revolution.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It was-- it-- it was-- the revolution was Communist aims, but eventually was-- was then controlled by the Social Democrats, who-- who established a democratic republic.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And all these nationalistic people, many of them wanted to have the monarchy back.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Although the monarchy had-- had led them into the disastrous World War.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And of course, the Jews were blamed for the loss of the war.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "It was called the stab in the back, the [SPEAKING GERMAN].",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "The stab in the-- the stab in the back.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "So you stab with knife, you know, in the back, meant the Jews, the internationally Jewry.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "You know.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And everything was blamed on the Jews.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
